# Cursor Entry Rules

This repo is the Dramatica-Informed Writing Assistant.

Before editing, Cursor must read `AGENTS.md`, relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, and the task-relevant roadmap docs. `docs/master_plan.md` is the current source of truth for roadmap direction and constraints.

The app is analysis-only. The assistant must never write, rewrite, continue, imitate, polish, improve, expand, or extend story prose.

Preserve the standard refusal message exactly:

`I can analyze structure and ask diagnostic questions, but I cannot write or rewrite story prose.`

OMI candidates are not canon. Approved project truth must come only from owner-approved memory/canon records.

Do not stage, commit, or push unless the user explicitly asks.

Run required Git/preflight/validation commands directly in the WSL shell; do not route them through LeanCTX or MCP tooling.

Use Graphify and Repomix context before broad raw search or large edits. Use LeanCTX where available for context-efficient navigation.
